HEADWORD: Phlegmon
<hw>Phleg"mon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>phlegmone</ets>, <ets>phlegmon</ets>, inflammation beneath the
skin, Gr. <grk>flegmonh`</grk>, fr. <grk>fle`gein</grk> to burn: cf. F.
<ets>phlegmon</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Purulent inflammation
of the cellular or areolar tissue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phlegmonous</ent>⟦br⟧
